00:43:42.530 --> 00:43:44.710
But then I became
lactose intolerant.

00:43:44.710 --> 00:43:46.950
So it's uncomfortable
for everyone involved.

00:43:46.950 --> 00:43:48.870
How do you still
enjoy French cooking,

00:43:48.870 --> 00:43:50.330
but not be able to handle cream?

00:43:50.330 --> 00:43:53.120
DAVID LEBOVITZ: I'm
lactose intolerant.

00:43:53.120 --> 00:43:55.370
I actually, when I was
younger-- I've never told them,

00:43:55.370 --> 00:43:56.495
I'm telling this on camera.

00:43:56.495 --> 00:43:58.450
But they didn't know
what was wrong with me.

00:43:58.450 --> 00:44:00.040
I was doubled over in pain.

00:44:00.040 --> 00:44:00.870
I was like 12.

00:44:00.870 --> 00:44:04.630
And then I went to college, and
I took food science classes.

00:44:04.630 --> 00:44:07.720
I'm like, lactose
intolerant-- oh, that's me.

00:44:07.720 --> 00:44:10.460
And I stopped drinking
milk by the glass.

00:44:10.460 --> 00:44:13.310
And I mean, I'm not an expert.

00:44:13.310 --> 00:44:15.520
But most lactose
intolerants can tolerate

00:44:15.520 --> 00:44:17.800
a certain amount of dairy.

00:44:17.800 --> 00:44:20.250
I can eat ice
cream, and so forth.

00:44:20.250 --> 00:44:22.840
Hard mountain cheeses,
there's very little,

00:44:22.840 --> 00:44:24.080
if any lactose in them.

00:44:24.080 --> 00:44:27.250
It's all been, I don't
quite know the process.

00:44:27.250 --> 00:44:31.170
But old cheeses, crumbly
cheeses, don't have lactose.

00:44:31.170 --> 00:44:32.410
Goat milk, yogurt.

00:44:32.410 --> 00:44:34.590
I love goat milk, I
love sheep's milk.

00:44:34.590 --> 00:44:38.280
Those, the lactose
is broken down.

00:44:38.280 --> 00:44:40.200
I actually don't
like cream sauces.

00:44:40.200 --> 00:44:42.370
I don't like stuff
that's swimming in cream.

00:44:42.370 --> 00:44:44.060
I like butter a lot.

00:44:44.060 --> 00:44:46.500
Butter in France is
cultured, so I can eat that.

00:44:46.500 --> 00:44:47.670
So move to France.

00:44:50.320 --> 00:44:52.780
